Wash and dry produce. Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}(drained, reserving liquid); roughly chop pineapple. Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced).

== Pickled Onion ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine onion, juice from half the lime, 2 tsp reserved pineapple juice, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 4 tsp pineapple juice, 1/2 tsp sugar, and 1/2 tsp salt.

== Pineapple Salsa ==

In a #second small bowl{}, combine chopped pineapple, tomato, and half the cilantro. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Cilantro-Lime Drizzle ==

In a #separate small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{2%tablespoon}, remaining cilantro, and as much lime zest as you like. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

== Plant-Based Protein ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Tex-Mex ground plant-based protein{8%ounce}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and cook until browned all over and warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> Cover pan if protein starts to splatter!

Turn off heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

== Tostadas ==

Meanwhile, drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with 1 tsp oil; brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer. Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Bake on top rack, carefully flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, divide between two baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks, flipping tortillas and swapping baking sheet positions halfway through toasting.

> Watch carefully—tortillas brown fast!

== Assembly ==

Divide tortillas between plates. Top with plant-based protein, pineapple salsa, and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Drizzle with cilantro-lime drizzle. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Plant-based protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.